members.name: WorkerNavigator.connection
members.description: Provides a NetworkInformation object containing information about the network connection of a device.

members.name: WorkerNavigator.permissions
members.description: Returns a Permissions object that can be used to query and update permission status of APIs covered by the Permissions API.

members.name: Navigator.storage
members.description: Returns a StorageManager interfaceÂ for managing persistance permissions and estimating available storage.

members.name: NavigatorID.appCodeName
members.description: Always returns 'Mozilla', in any browser. This property is kept only for compatibility purposes.

members.name: NavigatorID.appName
members.description: Returns the official name of the browser. Do not rely on this property to return the correct value.

members.name: NavigatorID.appVersion
members.description: Returns the version of the browser as a string. Do not rely on this property to return the correct value.

members.name: NavigatorConcurrentHardware.hardwareConcurrency
members.description: Returns the number of logical processor cores available.

members.name: NavigatorLanguage.language
members.description: Returns a DOMString representing the language version of the browser. The null value is returned when this is unknown.

members.name: NavigatorLanguage.languages
members.description: Returns an array of DOMStrings representing the languages known to the user, in order of preference.

members.name: NavigatorOnLine.onLine
members.description: Returns a Boolean indicating whether the browser is online.

members.name: NavigatorID.platform
members.description: Returns a string representing the platform of the browser. Do not rely on this property to return the correct value.

members.name: NavigatorID.product
members.description: Always returns 'Gecko', on any browser. This property is kept only for compatibility purposes.

members.name: NavigatorID.userAgent
members.description: Returns the user agent string for the current browser.

members.name: WorkerNavigator.sendBeacon()
members.description: Used to asynchronously transfer a small amount of data using HTTP from a Worker to a web server.

parameters.name: url
parameters.description: The url parameter indicates the resolved URL to which the data is to be transmitted.

parameters.name: data
parameters.description: The data parameter is a ArrayBufferView, Blob, DOMString, or FormData object containing the data to be transmitted.
